<br>
1. Scenerio - Minding by own business, say I'm running from the port in Surefall to Qeynos. I pass a young male elf who stops and sends me a hail. I stop my running, turn around and say hello back to the fella then I stand there and wait for him to type whatever he's going to ask me. I'm not a fast typer so I know it takes a minute to get a sentence out, I'm patient. Then I wait, and I wait, and I wait, thinking, &quot;Wow, this is going to be a long sentence or something&quot;. I wait some more, a few minutes go by. Finally, I get, &quot;Alright, see ya around&quot;. Then he runs off.<br>
<br>
WTF? Why the hell do people do this? Don't hail me for no reason whatsoever, then stand there and expect me to start a conversation for you. This happens alot if it looks like I'm just standing somewhere too. They come up say hello, I say hello back then they just stand there expecting me to entertain them. I don't mind at all people coming up out of the blue to RP a bit, or maybe say that they've seen me around and just wanted to chat a bit, heck anything. I enjoy talking to new people, but don't just stand there and expect me to entertain you. Starting a conversation consists of more than you saying hello then standing there. Give me a little more to work with, sheesh. Do a jig, make a joke, anything! <br>
<br>
2. This one is kind of related but from the opposite perspective. Just because someone is say, standing accross from the bank in Halas or sitting off in a corner by themselves does not mean they are just staring at their screen doing nothing. If you come up and and ask someone a question and they don't answer with more than a hello in 3 seconds, don't just run off, sheesh.  This usually happens when I'm right in the middle of some really long, silly sentence I'm typing to a friend and I don't want to cut it short. By the time I finish that sentence and start an answer to these people, they run off with a &quot;Thanks for nothing&quot;. Sheesh! <br>
People are very rarely just standing around by themselves doing absolutely nothing, they are either talking to their friends, their guild or working on their trade skills, and it may take a second to notice that someone has spoken to them or asked them a question. You may be in some kind of I'm-in-a-super-fast-hurry-speak-to-me-NOW world, but I friend, have my own pace and am not a speed typer, so wait a second and don't make me feel rude for not answering you within a millisecond. <br>
<br>
/shakes fist at Ichi!<br>
<br>
This is your fault Ichi! Now I'm all red and puffed in the face full of righteousness and self-importance over the people that annoy me :P <p>Narie<br>
